OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1781104294
OL,3,CHow Trump's oil blockade is pushing
OL,4,CCuba to the brink
OL,6,FUS Correspondent Dan Rivers sits down
OL,7,Fwith Cuban Government Minister,
OL,8,FAlejandro Garcia del Toro, Deputy
OL,9,FDirector General of the United States
OL,10,FDivision, Ministry of Foreign Affairs
OL,12,FOften, the outages last for more than
OL,13,F24 hours, putting life on hold for
OL,14,Fthose affected.
OL,16,FCuba has endured decades of sanctions
OL,17,Fand trade restrictions, but the
OL,18,Fchoking off of its oil supply, which
OL,19,Fcomes almost entirely from Venezuela
OL,20,Fand Mexico, has left the country on
OL,21,Fthe brink.
OL,26,@pD@Ort
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
