OL,3,CHow Trump's oil blockade is pushing
OL,4,CCuba to the brink
OL,6,FIt means many of the classic 1950s
OL,7,Fvehicles, which have become a
OL,8,Ftrademark of the tourist industry, lie
OL,9,Fstranded.
OL,11,FThose still operating are charging
OL,12,Feven higher prices for the dwindling
OL,13,Fnumber of tourists wandering around
OL,14,FHavana's historic streets.
OL,16,FThis week, we watched as international
OL,17,Fhotel chains were forced to change
OL,18,Ftheir names to avoid incurring US
OL,19,Fsecondary sanctions.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1781104294
OL,3,CHow Trump's oil blockade is pushing
OL,4,CCuba to the brink
OL,6,FMastercard and Visa have stopped
OL,7,Fworking here, and the currency is
OL,8,Fbecoming more worthless against the US
OL,9,Fdollar - the preferred currency for
OL,10,Fbusinesses.
OL,12,FWhat was once a popular tourist
OL,13,Fdestination is now largely deserted.
OL,14,FCafes are empty, and bands play
OL,15,Frenditions of the Buena Vista Social
OL,16,FClub hits to empty terraces.
OL,18,FTowers of rubbish are left rotting on
OL,19,Fmany street corners, some picked over
OL,20,Fby scavengers hoping to find a morsel
OL,21,Fof food or something worth salvaging.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
